TYPE 2,21,-1,20,BORDER,Stepping Through...
TYPE 3,20,10,40,NONE,One of the best ways to really see what each
TYPE 3,20,10,50,NONE,command does is to use the new single-step trace
TYPE 3,20,10,60,NONE,mode while running GRAAL. This is how to do it:
TYPE 3,20,10,75,NONE,1. Press the [G] key to call up the monitor.
TYPE 3,20,10,90,NONE,2. Click the <Trace> button.
TYPE 3,20,10,105,NONE,3. Click the <Back to GRAAL> button.
TYPE 3,20,10,120,NONE,4. Now all the commands and conditions GRAAL
TYPE 3,20,10,130,NONE,   executes will first be shown at the top of
TYPE 3,20,10,140,NONE,   the screen, waiting for a keypress from you.
TYPE 3,20,10,150,NONE,   (The full stop [.] key is recommended, 
TYPE 3,20,10,160,NONE,   because it also allows you to skip pauses.)
TYPE 3,20,10,175,NONE,5. To exit the trace mode, repeat steps 1-3.
TYPE 3,20,10,190,NONE,Enough of this. Go explore already!
